## Understanding the Issue

### Problem Description

In `src/deliver/send_proxy.cr`, two collection-emptiness checks use `.size > 0` instead of Crystal's idiomatic `.empty?` method. This is inconsistent with how the rest of the codebase handles the same pattern.

### Expected Behavior

Both checks should use Crystal's idiomatic style, matching the convention used throughout the rest of the codebase:

- Line 16: `unless endpoint.params.empty?`
- Line 19: `if !endpoint_hash["json"].empty?`

### Current Behavior

The file currently uses non-idiomatic checks:

- Line 16: `if endpoint.params.size > 0`
- Line 19: `body = if endpoint_hash["json"].size > 0`

### Affected Components

- `src/deliver/send_proxy.cr` — lines 16 and 19 only. No other files are involved.

